# tests/parity — the parity GRID (VISION §9.2, §9.6, B7). Two axes compose:
#
#                  Rust host          JS host
#     Rust kernel   ✓ (Phase A)        ✓ (Phase A)
#     Zig kernel    ✓ (Phase B)        ✓ (Phase B)
#
# Every cell runs the identical suite against real artifacts; any disagreement is a bug
# in a host, a kernel, or an UNDERSPECIFIED contract — all three worth catching. The
# two-kernel column is the Phase-B acceptance gate: the Zig kernel ships only when it
# matches the Rust kernel bit-for-bit on the shared e2e + conformance suite — by parity,
# never by inspection (B7). Amplified by record/replay (§15.1) and differential fuzzing
# (§15.2), both using the Rust kernel as the oracle.
#
# Phase A starts with the host↔host row (Rust kernel under both hosts); the kernel↔kernel
# rows light up in Phase B when //kernel/zig exists.
